---
// New page (Task 10): /privacy did not exist on the legacy site. Copy is the verbatim, approved
// text from .superpowers/sdd/task-10-content.md — do not paraphrase.
//
// One piece of the content file's /privacy copy is intentionally NOT rendered: the parenthetical
// "(We deliberately do not publish a specific privacy email until the client confirms one; the
// phone and contact form are the published channels for now.)" under "How to reach us about
// privacy" — that is a note to the implementer/client, not visitor-facing copy. The phone,
// address, and direction to the Contact page/form ARE rendered.
//
// This is a prose content page, not a marketing page, so it deliberately does NOT reuse the
// grey/white alternating section blocks or card styling from green-card.astro/index.astro — the
// task brief calls for "clean, readable prose... legibility matters most". What IS reused for
// visual consistency with the rest of the site:
// - The plain centered page-heading treatment from contact.astro (`contact-information__heading`
//   + `divider__contact`), instead of the big photo hero used on service pages — this page has
//   no form or call to action, so the photo hero's two-column layout doesn't apply.
// - `heading__section` for each subsection heading (centered, matching site convention).
// - `paragraph-section` for body copy, but WITHOUT the site's usual `align-middle` (centered)
//   treatment: centered multi-line text reads poorly for legal prose, so body paragraphs here are
//   left-aligned. This is a deliberate legibility choice, not a change to the copy itself.
// - `green-card green-card--list` for the short phone/address list, matching the bullet styling
//   used for similar short lists on about.astro.
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | Immigrant Resource Center"
  description="How Immigrant Resource Center collects, uses, and protects the information you
    share through this website."
  canonical="https://www.ircoffice.com/privacy"
>
  <section style="padding-top: 8rem; padding-bottom: 2rem;">
    <h1 class="contact-information__heading align-middle my-10">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <div class="divider__contact"></div>
    <p class="paragraph-section align-middle my-30 max-width-600">
      Last updated: July 2026. This policy explains what information this website collects and
      how it is used. It describes the website only; it is not a description of our full client
      intake process.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section style="padding-bottom: 3rem;">
    <h2 class="heading__section align-middle my-15">Information we collect</h2>
    <p class="paragraph-section my-20 max-width-600">
      This website collects personal information only when you choose to send it to us through a
      contact form. When you submit a form, we collect the <strong>name, email address, phone
      number, and message</strong> you provide. We use this information solely to respond to
      your enquiry.
    </p>
    <p class="paragraph-section my-20 max-width-600">
      We do not sell, rent, or share this information with third parties for their marketing,
      and we only share it with the service providers who help us operate the site and receive
      your message (described below).
    </p>
  </section>

  <section style="padding-bottom: 3rem;">
    <h2 class="heading__section align-middle my-15">How your message reaches us</h2>
    <p class="paragraph-section my-20 max-width-600">
      Form submissions are delivered to us by email through <strong>Resend</strong>, an email
      delivery service, and are protected against automated spam by
      <strong>Cloudflare Turnstile</strong>. These providers process your submission only to
      deliver it to us.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section style="padding-bottom: 3rem;">
    <h2 class="heading__section align-middle my-15">Analytics</h2>
    <p class="paragraph-section my-20 max-width-600">
      We use <strong>Cloudflare Web Analytics</strong> to understand, in aggregate, how visitors
      use the site (for example, which pages are viewed). Cloudflare Web Analytics is
      privacy-focused: it does <strong>not</strong> use cookies and does <strong>not</strong>
      collect personal information or track you across other websites.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section style="padding-bottom: 3rem;">
    <h2 class="heading__section align-middle my-15">Cookies</h2>
    <p class="paragraph-section my-20 max-width-600">
      This website does <strong>not</strong> set advertising or cross-site tracking cookies. Any
      storage used is limited to what is strictly necessary for the site and its spam protection
      to function.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section style="padding-bottom: 3rem;">
    <h2 class="heading__section align-middle my-15">Your choices</h2>
    <p class="paragraph-section my-20 max-width-600">
      You may contact us at any time to ask what information we hold about an enquiry you sent,
      or to ask us to delete it. Because form submissions reach us by email, deletion means
      removing the email we received.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section style="padding-bottom: 3rem;">
    <h2 class="heading__section align-middle my-15">How to reach us about privacy</h2>
    <p class="paragraph-section my-20 max-width-600">
      If you have any questions about this policy or about information you have shared with us,
      contact us using the form on our <a href="/contact" class="tab-text-link">Contact page</a>,
      or reach us directly at:
    </p>
    <ul class="green-card green-card--list my-35">
      <li><strong>Phone:</strong> (612) 822-5747</li>
      <li><strong>Address:</strong> 1 W Lake St Ste #165, Minneapolis, MN 55408</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!--section important notice (verbatim, legally load-bearing; deliberate reinforcement of the
      Footer's global Disclaimer, not a duplication to remove)-->
  <section style="padding-bottom: 10rem;">
    <h2 class="heading__section align-middle my-15">Important notice</h2>
    <p class="paragraph-section my-20 max-width-600">
      Immigrant Resource Center is a private entity that is registered in Minnesota and provides
      professional immigration and travel services at your direction. We are not a law firm or a
      substitute for an attorney or law firm, and we are not affiliated with USCIS or any
      government agency. We do not provide legal advice.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
